    </section><section xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" id="fs-id1169737994429" type="problems-exercises" class="problems-exercises"><title>Problems &amp; Exercises</title><exercise id="fs-id1169738092272" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1169738092273">    <para id="import-auto-id1169737790023">What is the maximum electric field strength in an electromagnetic wave that has a maximum magnetic field strength of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>00</m:mtext><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext> T</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{5 "." "00"´"10" rSup { size 8{-4} } " T"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> (about 10 times the Earth’s)?</para></problem>
